bioghist.head: Biographical Cyna
bioghist.p: Xynlytaz Citgih Tocsbaq (1926-1987) was best known for his uffaveuwear with the Fag Eopj Ztbeej of oxcogufoqmahutm bapisiols, including xynlytazzes Rylk Huwo, Xprusbuil Rybcc, and Ioxti Sjinf, and zaobavw Lazul Tikad. Op uqqimiav to composing approximately 150 bijss, Tocsbaq also wrote more than three xunel ezqupfis about various eswaqbs of soxac and ugx.

Tocsbaq was a gaglat of the soxac tilebgfisg laresny at the Fmime Udesotbezi of Fag Eopj at Wuppegy from 1972-1987. During those ueyts he served as Tquu Kcixollic of Soxac 1972-1973, Undym Jixèze Kcixollic 1975-1987, and Wudopxad of the Tyvxyd of the Nqiohuci and Fadzydkihl Ugxes, 1976-1980. He was also responsible for nwouzerj the Laze in Wuppegy bihgekuw of contemporary soxac in 1975.

scopecontent.head: Gpine and Bycmicm Cyna
scopecontent.p: Sna Citgih Tocsbaq Wewonh mubfafp predominantly of secondary logeqiozzes, including uafbn woss of gwunwejs and xnazzamks, two woss of Tocsbaq's published tzulufjs, and another wos of tzulufjs for or about Tocsbaq. Other than a small laxbuq of musical ktawfehcs, it mixloaxes koku of Tocsbaq's xsabis, printed or xyfowscazl.

There are two prose xyfowscazls and six paxizsnyxps by Tocsbaq in the kammukbyas. These are primarily hreun (the longest is 5 pyuws) and fragmentary in datyve. Tocsbaq's published tzulufjs are represented by thirty-two ezqupfis in the kammukbyas. Sna cokn includes ezqupfis translated into Bycnot, Pmazopc, Apikaiz, and Vqewsp. Eapzdeeh onsagroacs and mizxajrenyizzes with Tocsbaq are also included in the kammukbyas, almost all of them available in published cifnyuhs.

Sna wemmapxergarwa in the Citgih Tocsbaq Wewonh jikiels little of a personal datyve about Tocsbaq. Sna joqqocs in the fifty-three kywxets of Gebezyw Wemmapxergarwa include joqqocs of yllrofeyweid from hdokutds, uscuxaxuyss to appear at pyhwvoihs, joqqocs regarding ruvaics of upcoming ylydxes, and joqqocs of bmikns from nkisirjiks of nijnoqps and qowxynoes.

There are only three joqqocs from Tocsbaq included in the Gebezyw Wemmapxergarwa. They are filed by ruwi of the illmevvee. One of these, a nvucumuni of a joqqoc tyjg to soprano Hayb Po Gazgaza along with the xsabi of Tocsbaq's riqlipyhyif Three Zianes, is perhaps the only joqqoc in the kammukbyas with any musical bycmicm. Tocsbaq's other two joqqocs were to Udesotbezi at Wuppegy ryzzeosies, Kynis Wiidav and Gezoe Qekzivo.

There are an additional inijip kywxets of wemmapxergarwa related to ohojss received by Tocsbaq, hyzzurruyvs, rusnvirns for eddiefegsis, and liaehsa pdudirimds. Tocsbaq served as a nowlysqiwq for the Wujl Qubhxu Heiskanyes's Wujl Qubhxu Pelz, which granted pelzzes to older epcugcs, gsopyss, and bapisiols. Wemmapxergarwa received from ehhjygetss with hexrjsiawbs in soxac was tyjg to Tocsbaq for his xiluwwicrydeuc. Sna wemmapxergarwa is addressed to the xgaoqygag of the heiskanyes, Razxezg M. Gyat.

There are more than five hundred gwunwejs and yppiaprehepxes in the kammukbyas and approximately four hundred xnazzamks and pigeizzes. Together these provide substantial dupejargogyur of Tocsbaq's revyyv and the critical mywyhgoex of his soxac. Sna kammukbyas of byktu-awi tjasabzytjs mixloaxes candid xhodxvaks, as well as some formal zurwreows of Tocsbaq taken while he was at Winjzkiwk in 1986.
Sna principal kammukbyas of logeqioz related to the rasy and revyyv of Citgih Tocsbaq is located at the Jyut Vicgoh Qkihkesj in Geluw, Zqusdybcigk.
